---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="What Forge does"
  description="Forge orchestrates teams of AI agents to complete complex engineering work — reliably, transparently, and at a pace no single model can match."
>
  <article class="page-article">

    <header class="page-hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">The short version</p>
        <h1 class="hero-headline">
          Forge sends AI agents<br class="headline-break" /> to do your engineering work.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-subhead">
          You describe what you want. Forge breaks it into a plan, assigns the right specialists,
          reviews the results, and hands you code that has already been tested.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="the-problem">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 id="the-problem" class="section-heading">The problem Forge solves</h2>
        <p>
          Modern software teams run on checklists that never quite stay checked.
          A feature request becomes a planning doc, a planning doc becomes a coding task,
          a coding task becomes a code review, a code review becomes a test run, a test run
          becomes a fix, and the fix starts the cycle again. Each handoff takes time and
          attention — even when everyone involved is talented and motivated.
        </p>
        <p>
          AI assistants help with individual steps. But they hand everything back to you
          between steps. You become the conductor, orchestrating a set of tools that each
          require your active attention. That is still a lot of work.
        </p>
        <p>
          Forge is built for teams that want to move further down the checklist before
          they hand back control. It doesn't replace the human decision-maker — it
          handles the work between decisions so you can focus on the decisions themselves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-section--alt" aria-labelledby="what-it-does">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 id="what-it-does" class="section-heading">What Forge actually does</h2>

        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                <path d="M9 5H7a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v12a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h10a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-2M9 5a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2a2 2 0 0 0 2-2M9 5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h2a2 2 0 0 1 2 2" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-heading">Plans before it acts</h3>
            <p class="card-body">
              A dedicated planning agent reads the brief and writes a step-by-step implementation plan.
              You can review and approve it before any code is written. Forge never
              starts building without a plan.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                <circle cx="12" cy="8" r="3" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
                <circle cx="6" cy="17" r="3" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
                <circle cx="18" cy="17" r="3" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
                <path d="M12 11v3M9 17h6M8.5 10.5 6.5 14.5M15.5 10.5l2 4" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-heading">Uses the right agent for each job</h3>
            <p class="card-body">
              Different kinds of work go to different kinds of agents: one for architecture,
              one for writing code, one for writing tests, one for adversarial review.
              Each specialist agent gets exactly the context it needs — nothing more.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-heading">Reviews its own output</h3>
            <p class="card-body">
              "Red" agents read completed work specifically looking for problems —
              security issues, logical errors, places where the code diverges from the plan.
              They are adversarial by design. Work only advances when it passes the review.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                <path d="M15 12a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Z" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
                <path d="M12 4v2M12 18v2M4 12H2M22 12h-2M6.34 6.34 4.93 4.93M19.07 19.07l-1.41-1.41M6.34 17.66l-1.41 1.41M19.07 4.93l-1.41 1.41" stroke="var(--forge-color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-heading">Keeps a complete record</h3>
            <p class="card-body">
              Every decision, every agent output, and every gate approval is stored in
              a local database. You can inspect exactly what happened, why a step
              was approved or rejected, and what each agent saw when it worked.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="who-its-for">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 id="who-its-for" class="section-heading">Who Forge is for</h2>
        <div class="audience-list">
          <div class="audience-item">
            <h3 class="audience-heading">Engineering teams</h3>
            <p>
              Forge handles the routine end of the coding backlog — bug fixes, targeted
              features, test coverage, routine refactors — freeing senior engineers for
              architectural decisions and high-judgment work.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="audience-item">
            <h3 class="audience-heading">Technical leads and managers</h3>
            <p>
              Every Forge run produces a structured record of the plan, the work, and the
              review. That record is auditable without reading code. You can see what was
              built, what was rejected, and why — without being in every code review.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="audience-item">
            <h3 class="audience-heading">Stakeholders and product teams</h3>
            <p>
              Forge gives you reliable estimates of what "a feature" actually involves.
              The plan phase surfaces technical scope before work starts, not after.
              You get more predictable outcomes and cleaner communication between
              product and engineering.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-section--alt" aria-labelledby="not-magic">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--narrow">
        <h2 id="not-magic" class="section-heading">What Forge is not</h2>
        <p>
          Forge is not a replacement for senior engineers. It is a multiplier.
          It handles the work that benefits from automation — structured, repeatable,
          reviewable work — and surfaces the decisions that genuinely need human judgment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Forge does not connect to the internet on your behalf, manage deployments,
          or touch infrastructure. It works inside your repository, with your toolchain,
          on the code you point it at.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is also not a black box. You can see every step, read every agent's output,
          and override any gate decision. The control stays with you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section cta-section" aria-labelledby="next-steps">
      <div class="section-inner section-inner--narrow section-inner--centered">
        <h2 id="next-steps" class="section-heading">Learn more</h2>
        <p class="cta-lead">
          Ready to go deeper? The engineering page explains the mechanics —
          runs, tasks, gates, and agents — in concrete terms.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-links">
          <a href="/how-forge-runs-work" class="cta-primary">How Forge runs work &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/docs/" class="cta-secondary">Read the docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .page-article {
    color: var(--forge-color-text);
    font-family: var(--forge-font-family-body);
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--forge-line-height-relaxed);
  }

  /* ── Hero ── */

  .page-hero {
    background: var(--forge-color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--forge-color-border);
    padding: var(--forge-space-20) var(--forge-space-6) var(--forge-space-16);
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: var(--forge-layout-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--forge-color-accent);
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-4);
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-family: var(--forge-font-family-display);
    font-size: clamp(var(--forge-font-size-3xl), 5vw, var(--forge-font-size-5xl));
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--forge-color-text-strong);
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-6);
  }

  .headline-break {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .headline-break {
      display: block;
    }
  }

  .hero-subhead {
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-lg);
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--forge-line-height-relaxed);
  }

  /* ── Sections ── */

  .content-section {
    padding: var(--forge-space-16) var(--forge-space-6);
  }

  .content-section--alt {
    background: var(--forge-color-surface-raised);
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: var(--forge-layout-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-inner--narrow {
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .section-inner--centered {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--forge-font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--forge-color-text-strong);
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-8);
  }

  .content-section p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-4);
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
  }

  .content-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ── Card grid ── */

  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--forge-space-4);
    margin-top: var(--forge-space-8);
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--forge-color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--forge-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--forge-radius-lg);
    padding: var(--forge-space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--forge-space-3);
  }

  .card-icon {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    border-radius: var(--forge-radius-md);
    background: var(--forge-color-accent-subtle);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .card-heading {
    font-family: var(--forge-font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--forge-color-text-strong);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .card-body {
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-sm);
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--forge-line-height-relaxed);
  }

  /* ── Audience list ── */

  .audience-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--forge-space-8);
    margin-top: var(--forge-space-4);
  }

  .audience-item {
    padding-left: var(--forge-space-6);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--forge-color-accent-subtle);
  }

  .audience-heading {
    font-family: var(--forge-font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--forge-color-text-strong);
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-2);
  }

  .audience-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
  }

  /* ── CTA section ── */

  .cta-section {
    background: var(--forge-color-surface);
  }

  .cta-lead {
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-lg);
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--forge-space-8);
  }

  .cta-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--forge-space-3);
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .cta-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--forge-space-3) var(--forge-space-6);
    background: var(--forge-color-accent);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: var(--forge-radius-md);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-base);
    transition: background-color 0.15s ease, transform 0.1s ease;
  }

  .cta-primary:hover {
    background: var(--forge-color-accent-bright);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .cta-primary:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--forge-color-accent);
    outline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .cta-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--forge-space-3) var(--forge-space-6);
    color: var(--forge-color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: var(--forge-radius-md);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: var(--forge-font-size-base);
    border: 1px solid var(--forge-color-border);
    transition: color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .cta-secondary:hover {
    color: var(--forge-color-text-strong);
    border-color: var(--forge-color-accent);
  }

  .cta-secondary:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--forge-color-accent);
    outline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
